Don't feel like you are the only one. I had an abortion at the age of 18. I had a boyfriend (who is now my husband) we were only dating for about 2 months and he was a student trying to better his life. I was busy parting and being 18. I would have never been able to give up a child. I would have not been a good parent. I don't think that our relationship would have made it through the first year of the child life. So I would have been a single mother on welfare. <br>
We talk and think about that baby all the time. It is really hard because all three of my pregnancies I have thought how could I already love this child and not love the one we didn't keep. We have a lot of conflicting emotions. Honestly I cant say that I totally regret it. I know we wouldn't have the opportunities we have. After we had are first child and felt the strain of what a child brings. I know that we wouldn't have had a future together. Come on we were only dating for like 2 months.<br>
I have 2 awesome kids and one on the way that would not have happened. So no i cant say that totally regret the decision we made.<br>
I have a lot to say but having a really hard time articulating myself.<br>
Leah<br>
