<br>
Dag - abortion IS a consequence. It is one women must face as part of their options when pregnant. If it wasn't a consequence then none of those sharing their stories with us would still to this day have feelings about it. No woman is left without some lingering doubt or sadness. Its part and parcel. It doesn't make their choices wrong, however. Not facing the consequence would be the teen having the baby and then her parents raising the child as if it were their own. Then it becomes the parents (or grandparents really) consequence... for something they didn't even due. <br>
<br>
Right now I'm struggling with a way to approach my little sister on how she is doing. When we were home I got a feeling she is having difficulties coping with her choice even though it probably was the best for her. But I don't know how to approach her about it, I don't want to make matters worse for her. And with it being very long distance now I don't know what I can do. <br>
<br>
I'm just thankful she was able to have it done in a clean and safer enviroment. <br>
