It's true their are bad apples in both barrels. This is just a hot button issue for me. I have 7 nieces and nephews from unplanned pregnancies. The oldest is 29, the youngest is 11. One person could not live for 6 months on the collective &quot;child support&quot; they've received from all their neer-do-well &quot;fathers&quot; put together in their entire lives. My sisters bore ALL of the burdon, social, financial and emotional, for raising these kids. The first two of these pregnancies happened to my oldest sister when she was 15 and 17. The fathers were in their 20's and 30's respectively. Yes she was foolish, yes my parents should have put a chastity belt on her and tossed the key... By why did this little girl get stuck with everything while grown men who statutorily raped her just walked away - no shame, no child support payments, not even a stretchmark to pay for their &quot;fun&quot;?<br>
