I am pro-choice - You choose to practice safe sex or you choose to accept the consequences(not punishment- con sequence.) of your actions.  If I drive drunk and kill someone, it doesnt matter what the reasons behind it are.  I did something and there are natural consequences of those actions.<br>
<br>
As dag mentioned briefly, the LDS church opposes abortion, but allows for exceptions (not meaning they make the choice for the person but our doctrine accepts the following exceptions<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Rape, Incest, danger to the life of the mother and situations such as one of the ladies here described where the fetus was so malformed that life could not be sustained outside the womb.   <br>
<br>
The lifes of these fetuses are not any less valued, but in the situations of rape and incest, the woman was not involved in the choice or behavior that caused a pg against her will.    In the other situations, mom in danger, I think that is obvious, loose one or loose both.  In the last situation again, that life is going to end.  Why cause it to suffer unnecessarily.  We accept these exceptions , but encourage any woman, girl who finds herself in one of these situations to make the decision prayerfully.<br>
<br>
Until abortion is illegal, which may be never, I do think that every girl who would like to have an abortion should be educated as to the development of the fetus.  (A picture of where that fetus is along in development so that the decision can be an informed one, not based on the fallacy that the fetus is &quot;just a clump of cells.&quot;  <br>
<br>
I also think that any abortion procedure that&quot;rips&quot; the fetus apart should be outlawed as it is cruel and may cause inexplicable pain to the fetus (since they dont have a voice they cant tell us ,yet thy do have nerve cells so we must assume that they feel what is happening.)  I also would be happy to see late term and partial birth abortions banned (with the exceptions noted above)<br>
<br>
