<br>
I don't know what the differences are in the laws, but a lot of the perceptions about late-term abortion in the US are colored by pro-life rhetoric. My termination was at 20 weeks (fetal defects) and even so was difficult to obtain. I had to travel 2 hours away to a hospital in a major city, had to have ultrasounds done to confirm the fetus was less than 24 weeks (interestingly - that's the &quot;viability&quot; test which is assanine when you are carrying a non-viable fetus!). I had to sign consent forms and view fetal pictures and then wait 48 hours which meant driving back home, waiting through the weekend and then driving back again. (Like I hadn't already thought it through, like I was going to change my mind and decide to give birth so he could suffer and die of heart failure - give me a break!<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br>
<br>
Anyway, pro-lifers use terms like &quot;abortion on demand&quot; and &quot;partial birth abortion&quot; to make it sound like any woman, at any stage of pregnancy can just pop into a clinic during her lunch hour and say &quot;My skirt is too tight, I demand an abortion NOW!&quot; and they'd do it. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
They bring this up CONSTANTLY because of course, who would agree with aborting a viable baby? Nobody would, not even me, a total pro-choicer. They bring it up because it gives them the moral highground. But because they talk about it non-stop, it creates the perception that it's a common occurance when it just isn't happening at all.<br>
<br>
I challenge any pro-lifer who believes we have &quot;late term abortion on demand&quot; to call up the nearest women's clinic and tell them you're in the third trimester with a healthy normal pregnancy and you want an abortion. Just try it, then let us know if they tell you to come on in.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
The only women I have ever heard of having 3rd trimester abortions did so for severe, lethal defects. Period. NEVER have I heard of someone aborting a healthy fetus in the 3rd trimester. As far as 2nd trimester, they are rare and the majority of those abortions are done for girls under the age of 15 who were in denial about being pregnant; followed by married women terminating after very poor prenatal diagnosis. <br>
